      "writtenOn": "2026-04-07T16:51:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Confirmed from experimentation. `baudRate` property is set by constructor to https://github.com/openbmc/phosphor-modbus/blob/main/rtu/modbus/modbus.hpp#L41. So, the first time the constructor is called, it calls setProperties() with the passed baudrate and even parity: https://github.com/openbmc/phosphor-modbus/blob/main/rtu/modbus/modbus.cpp#L26.\nSo first ever call of setProperties from the constructor will always pass the `inBaudRate !\u003d baudRate` condition. \nSame thing for parity, its constructed with unknown https://github.com/openbmc/phosphor-modbus/blob/main/rtu/modbus/modbus.hpp#L42, so the first call with even https://github.com/openbmc/phosphor-modbus/blob/main/rtu/modbus/modbus.cpp#L26 is gauranteed to set this.",
      "parentUuid": "20d95fa7_7215265f",
